EPHEMERIDES - MINOR PLANETS:

AUTHORS :
	P. Rocher J. Chapront

ADDRESS :
	IMCCE - Observatoire de Paris
	Group: Dynamics of Solar System
	77 av. Denfert Rochereau, F-75014 PARIS
	Phone: 01 40 51 22 72
	Fax:   01 46 33 28 34
	e-mail: rocher@imcce.fr Jean.Chapront@imcce.fr

REFERENCES :
	Rocher P. and Chapront J. 1997, Compact Ephemerides for
	Minor Planets, Planetary and Space Science, To be published
_______________________________________________________________

DESCRIPTION : The observations of minor planets have been collected from Minor
	Planets Center. Numerical integrations have been performed and
	fitted to observations. Ephemerides of the equatorial heliocentric
	rectangular coordinates of the minor planets are presented under
	the form of Poisson series, covering 150 years from 1900.
	The list is presently limited to planets number: 1, 2, 3, 4, 5, 6,
	7, and 324 (Ceres, Pallas, Juno, Vesta, Astrae, Hebe, Iris and
	Bamberga).

CONTENTS : 2 types of files are provided:

	1 - Time series for heliocentric equatorial coordinates of
	    minor planets, as well as heliocentric and geocentric equatorial
	    rectangular coordinates of the Earth-Moon barycenter under the
	    same form which are necessary for geocentric positions.
	2 - Software: A FORTRAN program useful to read the series and
	    substitute the time. It computes geocentric positions.
	    An example of use is given.

